# AutoScope - Used Car Market Intelligence Dashboard

AutoScope is a Python-based analytics dashboard that analyzes real-world used car marketplace data to identify pricing trends, depreciation patterns, and potentially underpriced vehicle listings.

The project uses real used-car listing data and provides interactive filtering, analytics, and visualization tools to evaluate vehicle value more intelligently than simply comparing sticker prices.

---

## Features

* Real-world used vehicle dataset analysis
* Interactive dashboard built with Streamlit
* Vehicle filtering by:

  * Brand
  * Price
  * Mileage
  * Year
  * Body type
* Market trend analysis
* Deal scoring system
* Estimated market value calculations
* Underpriced vs overpriced vehicle detection
* Data visualizations using Matplotlib
* Real-time dashboard interaction

---

## Technologies Used

* Python
* Pandas
* Streamlit
* Matplotlib

---

## Dataset

This project uses a real used-car marketplace dataset sourced from Kaggle.

Dataset includes:

* Manufacturer
* Model
* Price
* Mileage
* Fuel type
* Transmission
* Vehicle type
* State
* Year

---

## How to Run

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/autoscope-car-market-analyzer.git
```

### 2. Navigate into the project folder

```bash
cd autoscope-car-market-analyzer
```

### 3. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install streamlit pandas matplotlib
```

### 4. Run the dashboard

```bash
python -m streamlit run app.py
```

---

## Project Goals

The purpose of this project is to combine:

* data analytics
* business intelligence
* visualization
* software development

into an interactive dashboard that simulates real-world market analysis tools.

